            <h2>Project Overview</h2>
            <p>This research examines the crucial balance between utilizing data-driven technologies for educational innovation and maintaining strong ethical protections for student data privacy. The research seeks to develop and recommend a comprehensive governance framework that enables educational institutions to benefit from artificial intelligence (AI) and big data analytics while protecting student privacy through proactive policies, technical safeguards, and increased cultural awareness.</p>
            
            <h3>Key Objectives</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Analyze the Central Dilemma between innovation and privacy</li>
                <li>Define the Data Privacy Landscape in Education</li>
                <li>Map the Regulatory Environment (FERPA, COPPA, GDPR)</li>
                <li>Propose a Proactive Governance Framework</li>
                <li>Provide Practical Guidelines to Stakeholders</li>
            </ul>
